International refugee system So what I want to do is take a step back and ask two very basic questions, which we all have to understand.
First, why is the existing system not working?
Second, how do we solve it?
The modern refugee system was developed after World War II.
It was originally intended to ensure that when a country collapses or worse, the regime is hostile to the people of that country, and that these people can have a place to go and live there safely and with dignity until they can return home.
