Through an international conference co-signed by 147 governments 1951 Convention relating to the Status of Refugees and an international organization, UNHCR, an international organization, committed to allowing others to enter their territories among member states to escape conflict and persecution.
But now the system is collapsing.
In theory, refugees have the right to seek asylum.
In reality, our immigration policy blocks this path to security.
In theory, refugees have the right to seek equal treatment or to choose to return to their home country.
But in practice they are trapped in a state of almost indefinite stagnation.
In theory, the refugee problem is the responsibility of all countries.
In fact, geographical location means that countries close to disputes are overloaded with the vast majority of refugees.
The rules of the original refugee system are not the cause of their collapse.
It’s that we’re not using it enough with the world that we need to rethink.
So I want to explain to you how today's system works.
How does the current refugee reception system work?
